---
description: Preserve the Useful Magic component system when editing React components.
globs: "components/**/*.tsx"
alwaysApply: false
---

# Component implementation

- Reuse `components/ui` primitives and existing section patterns before adding a component.
- Keep component APIs small, typed, and composable; avoid route-specific behavior in shared UI.
- Prefer semantic theme variables and existing utilities over arbitrary colors, spacing, or fixed dimensions.
- Provide the relevant states: default, hover, focus, active, disabled, loading, empty, and error.
- Confirm long copy, narrow viewports, keyboard use, and reduced motion do not break the component.
- Keep analytics calls explicit and stable. Never include personal or free-text values in event properties.
- A shared API or design-token change requires an explicit plan and reviewer approval.
